Kaduna State Police Command has apprehended individuals behind a planned sex party. Some youths had advertised the event on social media. It was scheduled to hold on December 27, 2020, starting from 8 pm, at a secret location. Male and female were to be naked all through the gathering. According to the invitation, interested participants must pay N2,000 (regular tickets), N5,000 (VIP), and N10,000 (VVIP). The information got to the State government and the police was ordered to go after the promoters. Police Public Relations Officer, ASP, Muhammad Jalige, confirmed that the venue was traced and arrests made. “We are investigating those behind the sex party and will soon give details of our findings,” Tribune quoted Jalige as saying.